com.solus.integrationlibrary.interfaces

Interface IWorkflowProccessListener


  • public interface IWorkflowProccessListener
    The main listener of the workflow process, which helps to control the whole process and track the process actions as abort, error or successful complete

      • onWorkflowError

        void onWorkflowError(java.lang.Throwable error,
                     java.lang.String workflowType,
                     java.lang.String userName)
        The method 'onWorkflowError()' calls when error was catched during the workflow process
        Parameters:
        error - instance of catched exception
        workflowType - type of workflow instance, on which the error was catched
        userName - name of user, for which the process was started
        See Also:

        Parameters:
        solusConfig - - configuration object, that contains license keys, OS information, etc. Notice, that it can be changed in the next versions of the integration library

      • onWorkflowCompleted

        void onWorkflowCompleted(java.lang.String workflowType,
                         java.lang.String userName,
                         boolean isDeviceBased)
        The method 'onWorkflowCompleted()' called when workflow process completes successfully
        Parameters:
        workflowType - type of workflow instance, which was aborted
        userName - name of user, for which the process was started
        isDeviceBased - true - if the workflow was started from the device, false - from the web application
